# Plugin Testing

After every rebuild, test using the Roblox Studio MCP server. Never skip this loop.

## Steps

1. Use the MCP server to run the frosting generator on **every MeshPart** in the scene.
2. Take a screenshot of each resulting mesh via the MCP server.
3. Analyze each screenshot — verify all of the following:
   - A visible flat border ring surrounds the raised center
   - The raised center (extruded top) has no missing or inverted faces
   - The frosting sits flush on the cookie surface (no gaps or z-fighting)
   - No geometry artifacts (overlapping verts, degenerate triangles)
4. If **any** mesh fails visual inspection, do NOT stop. Identify the issue, fix the code, rebuild, and re-test every mesh from scratch.
5. Only mark a change complete when all meshes pass.
